would you say humans are more strongly influenced by their experiences of suffering or their experiences of pleasure?

     if the former, is it fair to say a potential life of mostly pain and anguish is not worth creating? (note: if already existing, i do not mean worth continuing).
is there any meaning to the common pessimistic phrase: "life is suffering"?
given the fact that all life eventually dies, is life itself just a means to an end?
looking forward to your thoughts.
